      • setWithoutAscendingCheck

        public void setWithoutAscendingCheck(int bitToSet)
        For speed, this method sets bits at the given index, without checking that the bits are set in strictly ascending order. If the bits are not in ascending order, performance could be adversely affected.
        Parameters:
        bitToSet - index of the bit to set

      • set

        public void set(int bitToSet)
        Set the bit at the given index. Throws an exception if bits are not set in strictly ascending order. For performance reasons, bits must be set in ascending order.
        Parameters:
        bitToSet - The index of the bit to set.
